- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a cost-efficient auto-scaling system for cloud instances, which is relevant to computational finance. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the use of cloud instances for web application provisioning, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a fault-tolerant model and auto-scaling policies for web applications, which are relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a system for auto-scaling cloud instances, which is relevant to systems and control.
